# Cavari Production Readiness Checklist

Your website is currently in a **very strong position** for hosting. The design is premium, the code is functional, and I have just implemented the missing SEO layers.

To go live (Production Ready), follow these essential steps:

## 1. Environment Configuration (.env)
When you move to your live server (e.g., Hostinger, SiteGround, Forge, etc.), update your `.env` file:
- [ ] `APP_ENV=production`
- [ ] `APP_DEBUG=false`
- [ ] `APP_URL=https://yourdomain.com` (Crucial for SEO and links)
- [ ] `DB_DATABASE`, `DB_USERNAME`, `DB_PASSWORD` (Set your live database credentials)

## 2. Asset Compilation
Before deploying, you must build your CSS and JS for production:
- [ ] Run `npm run build` on your local machine or server.
- [ ] This creates a `public/build` folder with minified, optimized files.
- [ ] **Note:** Your `npm run dev` is for development only; production uses the files in `public/build`.

## 3. SEO Finalization (Already started!)
I have already implemented the following in your code:
- [x] **Open Graph Tags**: For beautiful sharing on WhatsApp, Facebook, and Instagram.
- [x] **Twitter Cards**: Optimized for X/Twitter sharing.
- [x] **Canonical URLs**: To prevent duplicate content issues.
- [x] **Robots Tags**: Directing search engines to index your pages.
- [x] **Dynamic Product SEO**: Each product page now pulls its own name and image for SEO.

**Action Required for you:**
- [ ] **Sitemap Update**: Open `public/sitemap.xml` and replace `http://localhost` with your actual domain `https://yourdomain.com`.
- [ ] **Favicon**: You have `images/cavarilogo.png` as a favicon. Ensure this file exists and looks good in the browser tab.

## 4. Laravel Production Optimization
Once the code is on the server, run these commands to make the site lightning fast:
- [ ] `php artisan config:cache`
- [ ] `php artisan route:cache`
- [ ] `php artisan view:cache`

## 5. Security & SSL
- [ ] Ensure your hosting has an **SSL Certificate** (HTTPS).
- [ ] Ensure `APP_URL` in `.env` starts with `https://`.

---

### Is it ready now??
**Yes.** Technically, the code is ready. Once you point your domain to the server and follow the checklist above, you are good to go!
